<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Iran and Pakistan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="169" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="169">
The male specimen from Pakistan, widely separated geographically from the localities in south Iran, is associated with 
<taxonomicName family="Galacticidae" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. schaeuffelei" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" rank="species" species="schaeuffelei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">H. schaeuffelei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by observing the presence of a forked R4 and R5 in the forewing, a character, which is unique and unknown from other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Minet" authorityYear="1986" class="Insecta" family="Galacticidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Galacticidae</taxonomicName>
in the region.
</paragraph>
